textBeforeTable: Football EWU BIG SKY CONFERENCE ALL-ACADEMIC SELECTIONS -- Fall 2010 The Eagles are the reigning champions of the Sterling Savings Bank Big Sky Conference Presidents’ Cup, which is unique in collegiate athletics in that it reinforces the league’s dedication to the academic side of the student-athlete experience. The winner of this award is determined by overall athletic success combined with team grade point averages, graduation rates, and All-Conference performers with grade point averages of at least 3.0. A total of 136 Big Sky All-Academic honors were won in the 2008-09 school year, and 122 in 2007-08. Last year, exactly 150 All-Academic honors were won by EWU student-athletes in the 2009-10 school year. In the fall, 20 were from football, 11 from volleyball, nine from women's soccer, seven from women's cross country and five from men's cross country. Selections in the winter included 16 from the women's track and field team, 16 from the men's squad, seven from women's basketball and five from men's basketball. In the spring, 20 honored student-athletes were from the men's track and field team, 18 came from the women's squad, seven from men's tennis, five from women's golf and four from women's tennis. To qualify for the team, student-athletes must have at least a 3.20 accumulative grade point average at EWU and must also have participated in at least half of the team's competitions.
